How NAT Works

When a private IP (like 192.168.1.2) sends data to internet:

1.Router replaces source IP with its public IP
2.Keeps mapping in NAT table
3.Internet replies come back to router
4.Router reverts back to private IP


Eg)
Before NAT: 192.168.1.2 → 8.8.8.8
After NAT : 200.1.1.1 → 8.8.8.8



